01:16:28,957 --> 01:16:31,551
- Is that satisfactory, Mr. Barris?
- Not entirely.

1193
01:16:31,716 --> 01:16:33,470
Though I wonder,
when I'm locked down...

1194
01:16:33,637 --> 01:16:37,153
...may I be provided with some lotion,
and perhaps some...?

1195
01:16:43,716 --> 01:16:48,666
So, what do you think
of Barris' evidence?

1196
01:16:50,556 --> 01:16:54,186
Seems like what he played...
The little we heard anyway.

1197
01:16:54,356 --> 01:16:56,667
...sounded pretty genuine to me.

1198
01:16:56,837 --> 01:17:00,432
It's fake. Worthless.

1199
01:17:00,597 --> 01:17:02,189
Made on a home computer.

1200
01:17:02,757 --> 01:17:04,554
Maybe you're right.

1201
01:17:06,356 --> 01:17:08,996
Is that my medical report
you have there?

1202
01:17:09,158 --> 01:17:10,556
Yep.

1203
01:17:11,516 --> 01:17:12,837
What does it say?

1204
01:17:14,278 --> 01:17:16,507
That you're completely bonkers.

1205
01:17:18,597 --> 01:17:20,029
Completely?

1206
01:17:20,757 --> 01:17:24,831
There's maybe two brain cells
that still light up.

1207
01:17:24,997 --> 01:17:26,748
Rest is just...

1208
01:17:26,917 --> 01:17:29,306
...short circuits and sparks.

1209
01:17:29,478 --> 01:17:31,149
Two?

1210
01:17:33,757 --> 01:17:38,149
Listen, when you go to pick up
your next paycheck...

1211
01:17:38,318 --> 01:17:41,787
...there will be a substantial difference
this time.

1212
01:17:41,957 --> 01:17:44,916
I get some sort of bonus for this...?

1213
01:17:45,078 --> 01:17:49,707
For this having happened to me on duty?

1214
01:17:49,877 --> 01:17:52,789
No. Read your penal code.

1215
01:17:52,957 --> 01:17:57,395
"An officer who willingly becomes an
addict and doesn't report it promptly...

1216
01:17:57,556 --> 01:17:59,594
...is subject to a misdemeanor charge...

1217
01:17:59,877 --> 01:18:02,595
...a fine, and/or six months".

1218
01:18:03,238 --> 01:18:05,752
You'll probably just be fined.

1219
01:18:05,917 --> 01:18:07,350
Willingly?

1220
01:18:08,478 --> 01:18:11,548
No one held a gun to your head
and shot you up.

1221
01:18:11,717 --> 01:18:13,628
No one dropped something in your soup.

1222
01:18:13,797 --> 01:18:16,708
You knowingly and willingly
took an addictive drug...

1223
01:18:16,877 --> 01:18:19,186
...brain-destructive and disorienting.

1224
01:18:19,358 --> 01:18:20,837
I had to.

1225
01:18:21,278 --> 01:18:23,632
You could have pretended to.

1226
01:18:23,797 --> 01:18:26,311
Most officers manage to cope with it.

1227
01:18:27,717 --> 01:18:32,507
And from the quantities
you were taking...

1228
01:18:32,677 --> 01:18:36,033
My God, Fred, I...

1229
01:18:36,198 --> 01:18:39,872
Hey, you know what I would do
if I were you?

1230
01:18:40,158 --> 01:18:43,229
Once you get out of New Path and,
you know, it's all over...

1231
01:18:43,398 --> 01:18:45,274
But it may never be over.

1232
01:18:47,557 --> 01:18:48,672
Cigarette?

1233
01:18:50,238 --> 01:18:53,274
I'm getting off that too. Everything.

1234
01:18:53,997 --> 01:18:56,228
Including chocolate. Yeah.

1235
01:18:57,118 --> 01:18:58,631
And...

1236
01:18:58,917 --> 01:19:00,670
Like I tell my kids...

1237
01:19:02,478 --> 01:19:05,355
I've got two kids. Two girls.

1238
01:19:06,118 --> 01:19:07,345
Little ones.

1239
01:19:10,118 --> 01:19:12,426
I don't believe you do.

1240
01:19:14,318 --> 01:19:16,354
You're not supposed to.

1241
01:19:17,518 --> 01:19:18,792
Maybe not.

1242
01:19:38,759 --> 01:19:42,273
Listen, is there anywhere specific
you'd like to go?

1243
01:19:43,639 --> 01:19:46,675
Maybe over to
Donna Hawthorne's place?

1244
01:19:46,837 --> 01:19:51,195
From the information you brought in,
sounds like you guys are pretty close.

1245
01:19:53,637 --> 01:19:55,435
Yes, we are.

1246
01:19:56,597 --> 01:19:57,826
How'd you know that?

1247
01:19:58,238 --> 01:20:00,957
Process of elimination.

1248
01:20:02,118 --> 01:20:03,436
I know who you aren't...

1249
01:20:03,878 --> 01:20:06,438
...and we're talking about
a very small group of people...

1250
01:20:06,597 --> 01:20:08,792
...that we hoped would lead us higher.

1251
01:20:08,957 --> 01:20:10,630
And maybe Barris will.

1252
01:20:10,917 --> 01:20:14,592
I pieced it together a long time ago
that you're Arctor.

1253
01:20:17,958 --> 01:20:19,755
I'm who?

1254
01:20:22,637 --> 01:20:24,675
I'm Bob Arctor?

1255
01:20:28,118 --> 01:20:30,712
Yeah, get me
Donna Hawthorne's number...

1256
01:20:30,877 --> 01:20:33,153
...or just patch me through
when you locate her.

1257
01:20:34,038 --> 01:20:35,231
Thanks.

1258
01:20:35,398 --> 01:20:38,833
Bud, you are in a very bad way,
my friend.

1259
01:20:38,997 --> 01:20:40,909
Maybe Jim Barris poisoned you.

1260
01:20:41,078 --> 01:20:43,591
We're really interested in Barris,
not you.

1261
01:20:43,757 --> 01:20:47,228
The whole scanning of the house
was to keep an eye on him.

1262
01:20:47,398 --> 01:20:52,551
We hoped to draw him here, and we did.

1263
01:20:53,198 --> 01:20:57,350
He is deep into it
with some very dangerous people.

1264
01:20:58,677 --> 01:21:02,114
Then I'm a what?

1265
01:21:02,278 --> 01:21:04,632
Well, we had to get to Barris
to set him up.

1266
01:21:04,797 --> 01:21:06,835
So how we arranged it was...

1267
01:21:06,997 --> 01:21:09,831
...he grew progressively
more and more suspicious...

1268
01:21:09,997 --> 01:21:11,716
...that you were an undercover cop...

1269
01:21:11,877 --> 01:21:14,268
...trying to nail him
or use him to get high or...

1270
01:21:14,438 --> 01:21:17,668
So he did what you or anyone
would have done.

1271
01:21:17,957 --> 01:21:19,028
Hey, Donna.

1272
01:21:19,399 --> 01:21:23,106
Yeah, hi, this is a buddy of Bob's.
Arctor.

1273
01:21:24,118 --> 01:21:25,311
Yeah.

1274
01:21:25,478 --> 01:21:29,516
Listen, he's in a... He's in a bad way.

1275
01:21:30,757 --> 01:21:32,988
Yeah, way bad.

1276
01:21:33,158 --> 01:21:36,993
I was wondering if I could
ask a favor of you.

1277
01:21:38,037 --> 01:21:39,233
You're a sweetheart.

1278
01:21:39,797 --> 01:21:43,269
Yeah, I'm sure he'll
appreciate it very much.

1279
01:21:43,438 --> 01:21:45,828
Great, thanks. Good news.

1280
01:21:45,997 --> 01:21:49,911
Donna Hawthorne said she'd pick you up
out front in about five minutes.

1281
01:21:52,439 --> 01:21:54,952
You fuckers.

1282
01:22:52,398 --> 01:22:54,912
You're a good man, Bob.

1283
01:22:55,478 --> 01:22:57,752
You've been dealt a bad deal.

1284
01:22:57,918 --> 01:23:01,672
This is not fair, but it has to be this way.

1285
01:23:01,838 --> 01:23:03,065
You just...

1286
01:23:03,238 --> 01:23:07,152
You gotta... You gotta just wait it out,
just get through it.

1287
01:23:07,319 --> 01:23:09,354
And someday...

1288
01:23:09,837 --> 01:23:12,306
...a long time from now...

1289
01:23:12,838 --> 01:23:14,556
...you'll see the way you saw before.

1290
01:23:15,759 --> 01:23:18,431
There'll be a recognition...

1291
01:23:18,599 --> 01:23:23,719
...and some spark in a disguised form...

1292
01:23:23,878 --> 01:23:25,835
...will reveal itself to you...

1293
01:23:26,719 --> 01:23:28,913
...and guide you.

1294
01:23:53,238 --> 01:23:55,672
- Substance D?
- Yeah.

1295
01:23:56,319 --> 01:23:58,115
Ate his head.

1296
01:23:58,278 --> 01:23:59,997
Another loser.

1297
01:24:00,838 --> 01:24:02,475
It's easy to win.

1298
01:24:04,359 --> 01:24:06,110
Anybody can win.

1299
01:24:14,478 --> 01:24:16,150
Goodbye.

1300
01:24:24,158 --> 01:24:28,118
Living and unliving things
are exchanging properties.

1301
01:24:28,958 --> 01:24:34,192
The drive of unliving things is stronger
than the drive of living things.

1302
01:24:36,559 --> 01:24:41,314
The living should never be used
to serve the purposes of the dead.

1303
01:24:42,599 --> 01:24:46,637
But the dead should, if possible...

1304
01:24:46,798 --> 01:24:50,109
...serve the purposes of the living.

1305
01:25:05,599 --> 01:25:06,952
Hey, good news.

1306
01:25:07,118 --> 01:25:09,427
I think I got you transferred
to one of our farms.

1307
01:25:09,798 --> 01:25:12,711
- Can I work with animals?
- I think you'll be working with plants...

1308
01:25:12,878 --> 01:25:15,551
...for a while. In the open,
where you can touch the ground.

1309
01:25:15,719 --> 01:25:18,631
- I wanna be with something living.
- The ground is living.

1310
01:25:18,798 --> 01:25:20,835
The earth is still alive.

1311
01:25:20,998 --> 01:25:23,512
Do you have
any agricultural background?

1312
01:25:23,679 --> 01:25:25,112
I worked in an office.

1313
01:25:26,038 --> 01:25:28,189
Well, you'll be outside from now on.

1314
01:25:51,479 --> 01:25:53,117
Your name is Bruce.

1315
01:25:53,279 --> 01:25:55,349
My name is Bruce.

1316
01:25:55,520 --> 01:25:59,592
We're gonna try you on farming
for a period, Bruce.

1317
01:25:59,759 --> 01:26:03,389
- Okay.
- Staff thought you'd be better off.

1318
01:26:03,559 --> 01:26:05,708
I think you'll like it here.

1319
01:26:05,878 --> 01:26:08,073
I think I'll like it here.

1320
01:26:09,118 --> 01:26:11,757
Come on, I'll show you
where you're gonna be sleeping.

1321
01:26:12,759 --> 01:26:14,829
You like mountains, Bruce?

1322
01:26:14,998 --> 01:26:16,194
Look up.

1323
01:26:16,359 --> 01:26:17,917
Mountains.

1324
01:26:18,078 --> 01:26:20,832
No snow, but mountains.

1325
01:26:20,998 --> 01:26:22,591
I like mountains.

1326
01:26:22,759 --> 01:26:24,988
The air is good here.

1327
01:26:25,479 --> 01:26:27,275
I like air.

1328
01:26:28,078 --> 01:26:29,273
Yeah.

1329
01:26:29,439 --> 01:26:32,590
We all like air, Bruce. We really do.

1330
01:26:32,759 --> 01:26:34,988
That we have in common.

1331
01:26:37,960 --> 01:26:39,711
4G.

1332
01:26:39,878 --> 01:26:41,631
Yours is 4G. Can you remember that?

1333
01:26:41,798 --> 01:26:43,390
4G.

1334
01:26:45,519 --> 01:26:47,237
Will I be seeing my friends?

1335
01:26:47,798 --> 01:26:50,108
What, you mean
from back where you were?

1336
01:26:50,279 --> 01:26:51,917
The Santa Ana facility?

1337
01:26:53,238 --> 01:26:54,592
Mike and Laura...

1338
01:26:54,759 --> 01:26:58,149
...and Mike and Eddie. And...

1339
01:26:58,319 --> 01:27:00,514
The people from
the residence facilities...

1340
01:27:00,679 --> 01:27:02,954
...they don't come out
to the farms, Bruce.

1341
01:27:03,118 --> 01:27:06,429
- See, these are closed operations.
- Closed operations.

1342
01:27:06,599 --> 01:27:09,556
But, you know,
you might get back up there...

1343
01:27:09,719 --> 01:27:11,231
...couple times a year.

1344
01:27:11,399 --> 01:27:13,868
You know,
there are gatherings at Christmas...

1345
01:27:14,038 --> 01:27:15,676
...and the next one is Thanksgiving.

1346
01:27:15,838 --> 01:27:16,988
Thanksgiving.

1347
01:27:17,159 --> 01:27:20,230
So you might see them in three months.

1348
01:27:33,198 --> 01:27:34,996
Hey, Audrey.

1349
01:27:35,199 --> 01:27:37,155
Glad you could meet.

1350
01:27:38,038 --> 01:27:40,952
So tell me, are they
getting paranoid about him?

1351
01:27:41,118 --> 01:27:43,587
No, not at all. The guy's so burnt-out.

1352
01:27:45,319 --> 01:27:47,880
And we're still convinced
they're growing the stuff?

1353
01:27:48,198 --> 01:27:50,872
They have to be. Who else?

1354
01:27:52,199 --> 01:27:55,077
I just wonder
if it even matters at this...

1355
01:27:55,238 --> 01:27:58,390
It matters, Audrey.

1356
01:27:58,559 --> 01:28:01,471
It matters when we can prove
that New Path is the one growing...

1357
01:28:01,639 --> 01:28:03,391
...manufacturing and distributing.

1358
01:28:04,838 --> 01:28:06,751
How does he look?

1359
01:28:07,519 --> 01:28:10,591
I mean, do you think he's gonna
be able to pull through for us?

1360
01:28:10,760 --> 01:28:13,353
All we can do is hope
that when he finally gets in there...

1361
01:28:13,519 --> 01:28:18,114
...a few charred brain cells will flicker on
and some distant instinct will kick in.

1362
01:28:18,279 --> 01:28:19,712
It's just...

1363
01:28:20,319 --> 01:28:23,833
- It's just such a cost to pay.
- Yeah.

1364
01:28:24,199 --> 01:28:26,270
But there's no other way to get in there.

1365
01:28:26,439 --> 01:28:29,318
I couldn't, and think how long I tried.

1366
01:28:29,679 --> 01:28:31,270
They got that place locked up tight.

1367
01:28:31,439 --> 01:28:34,555
They're only gonna let a burnt-out husk
like Bruce in.

1368
01:28:34,719 --> 01:28:38,074
Harmless. You have to be,
or they won't take the risk.

1369
01:28:38,239 --> 01:28:40,958
Yeah, but to sacrifice someone...

1370
01:28:41,118 --> 01:28:44,157
...a living person,
without them ever knowing it.

1371
01:28:44,319 --> 01:28:47,435
I mean, if he'd understood,
if he had volunteered...

1372
01:28:47,600 --> 01:28:49,430
...but he doesn't know and he never did.

1373
01:28:49,600 --> 01:28:51,670
He didn't volunteer for this.

1374
01:28:51,840 --> 01:28:54,273
Sure he did. It was his job.

1375
01:28:54,439 --> 01:28:56,715
It wasn't his job to get addicted.

1376
01:28:57,599 --> 01:28:59,271
We took care of that.

1377
01:28:59,439 --> 01:29:01,475
Look, Mike, I gotta get out.

1378
01:29:01,639 --> 01:29:03,835
I can't do this again.

1379
01:29:03,998 --> 01:29:06,796
I want it to end. I...

1380
01:29:06,958 --> 01:29:09,554
I lay in bed at night, and I can't sleep,
and I just think:

1381
01:29:09,719 --> 01:29:13,314
- "Shit, we are colder than they are".
- I don't think so.

1382
01:29:13,479 --> 01:29:16,278
I mean, I believe God's m. o.
is to transmute evil into good...

1383
01:29:16,439 --> 01:29:19,078
...and if he's active here,
he's doing that now...

1384
01:29:19,238 --> 01:29:21,470
...although our eyes can't perceive it.

1385
01:29:21,640 --> 01:29:24,711
The whole process is hidden
beneath the surface of our reality...

1386
01:29:24,880 --> 01:29:27,346
...will only be revealed later.

1387
01:29:27,920 --> 01:29:29,637
And even then...

1388
01:29:29,800 --> 01:29:31,916
...the people of the future...

1389
01:29:32,078 --> 01:29:35,515
...our children's children
will never truly know...

1390
01:29:35,680 --> 01:29:39,274
...this awful time that we have
gone through and the losses we took.

1391
01:29:40,960 --> 01:29:43,997
Well, maybe some footnote
in a minor history book.

1392
01:29:45,239 --> 01:29:47,707
A brief mention
with no list of the fallen.

1393
01:30:32,199 --> 01:30:34,430
You're seeing the flower of the future.

1394
01:30:35,039 --> 01:30:38,190
- But not for you, Bruce.
- Not for me.

1395
01:30:38,479 --> 01:30:40,868
No, you've had too much
of a good thing already.

1396
01:30:42,079 --> 01:30:44,957
Get up, get up. Stop worshipping.

1397
01:30:45,119 --> 01:30:47,792
This isn't your god anymore,
although it once was.

1398
01:30:48,838 --> 01:30:50,319
Gone.

1399
01:30:51,159 --> 01:30:53,036
Flowers gone.

1400
01:30:53,199 --> 01:30:55,077
No, you just can't see them.

1401
01:30:55,239 --> 01:30:56,912
Back to work.

1402
01:30:59,960 --> 01:31:01,313
I saw.

1403
01:31:02,199 --> 01:31:04,667
Back to work, Bruce.

1404
01:31:08,640 --> 01:31:11,791
I saw death rising from the earth...

1405
01:31:13,399 --> 01:31:15,755
...from the ground itself...

1406
01:31:17,399 --> 01:31:21,756
...in one blue field.

1407
01:31:26,479 --> 01:31:29,278
A present for my friends...

1408
01:31:29,800 --> 01:31:31,836
...at Thanksgiving.
